<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Docs on Avatar Optimizer (1.9.16-beta.2)</title><link>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/</link><description>Recent content in Docs on Avatar Optimizer (1.9.16-beta.2)</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Basic Concepts</title><link>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/basic-concept/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/basic-concept/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="basic-concepts"&gt;
 Basic Concepts of Avatar Optimizer
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#basic-concepts"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This page describes the basic concepts of Avatar Optimizer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-avatar-optimizer"&gt;
 What is Avatar Optimizer?
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#what-is-avatar-optimizer"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avatar Optimizer is a non-destructive tool that helps you optimize your avatar.
This tool is initially designed for VRChat avatars, but it might be usable for other Avatars supported by &lt;a href="https://ndmf.nadena.dev/"&gt;NDMF&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non-destructive means (in Avatar Optimizer):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t have to unpack your prefab to apply Avatar Optimizer.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What you have to do is adding component.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avatar Optimizer doesn&amp;rsquo;t affects avatar saved in your project, only affects temporal copy of avatar for building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that non-VRChat avatar support is generally community-based and may not be supported by the Avatar Optimizer dev team.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Frequently Asked Questions</title><link>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/faq/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/faq/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="faq"&gt;
 Frequently Asked Questions
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#faq"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is the list of frequently asked questions about Avatar Optimizer.
If you have some other questions, please feel free to ask on the &lt;a href="https://github.com/anatawa12/AvatarOptimizer/discussions"&gt;GitHub Discussions&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://discord.gg/dV4cVpewmM"&gt;NDMF Discord&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="https://misskey.niri.la/@anatawa12"&gt;Fediverse (Misskey / Mastodon)&lt;/a&gt;.
I&amp;rsquo;m usually use Japanese, but you can ask me with English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="avatar-behavior-or-appearance-changed-when-using-aao-trace-and-optimize-component"&gt;
 The behavior or appearance of the avatar is changed when using &lt;code&gt;AAO Trace and Optimize&lt;/code&gt; component
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#avatar-behavior-or-appearance-changed-when-using-aao-trace-and-optimize-component"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the behavior or appearance of the avatar is changed when using &lt;code&gt;AAO Trace and Optimize&lt;/code&gt; component, it is always a bug unless you depend on bugs in other components of Avatar Optimizer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Bug Report Helper</title><link>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/bug-report-helper/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/bug-report-helper/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bug-report-helper"&gt;
 Bug Report Helper
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#bug-report-helper"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you find a bug in AAO: Avatar Optimizer, we appreciate it if you could report it to us. &lt;br&gt;
To help us understand and fix the bug, information about your avatar and environment is useful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To help you provide such information, AAO: Avatar Optimizer includes a Bug Report Helper window,
which collects information about your avatar and environment into a report file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the tool does not collect all information but only general basic information about your avatar,
to prevent license violations and privacy issues.&lt;br&gt;
Therefore, you may be asked to provide more information about avatar.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Changelog</title><link>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/changelog/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://vpm.anatawa12.com/avatar-optimizer/beta/en/docs/changelog/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="changelog"&gt;
